data.description: Rare Offering, The Beautiful Jelly House is waiting for her new owner, in the heart of Carolina Beach. Embrace and Retreat, from your Turkish Steam Spa to your Cozy Balcony and Listen to the Ocean Waves while gently breathing in the healing salt air under a moonlit sky. Nestled 2.5 blocks from the boardwalk on Raleigh Avenue which is known for its historic Bungalows of a time past, sits a rare Gem whose architectural design blends the perfection of a Hamptons Sea Shore Bungalow with a touch of Coastal Modern. Originally Built In 1949 the new owners embraced her good bones and began the transformation of a lifetime in 2017 with a fully updated completion in 2020. The Handmade Craftmanship was completed by Master Builders J. Long Custom Homes, known for their quality and skill with Historic Renovations and New Homes. Not many homes on the island have such Quality Materials and Energy Efficiency as this one. Well-Manicured Outdoors, that offers Patinated Copper Landscape Lighting,  custom Ipe Semi- Enclosed Copper Sea Shower. Ipe and Stucco European Planters and Fragrant Jasmine, Wispy Palms, Privacy Hedges.  Make an Appointment to see the beautiful aesthetics and the key finishes and design elements that give this beautiful beach home its unique look and feel.  Owner is BrokerAdditional Features: Ipe Decking and WalkwaysShip Lap Ceilings and WallsPecky Cyprus Trim Accents Hand forged Cast Iron Handrail Custom StairsStep Lighting Master Bath:Steam Spa  Curb To Ceiling Shower Glass Cle' Cement TilesT&G Vaulted CeilingAcacia Wood Vanity with Concrete Top Phylrich Polished Nickel Wall Mount Faucets Master Bedroom: Tongue and Groove Ceiling with Reclaimed Cyprus Beams Wall -Wall/Floor to Ceiling Custom Built in Vanity Closet. Lender Anthony Gallop Offering Options: 1. 2k Credit at Closing2. Appraisal Credit at Closing 3. 1% Temporary Rate Buydown first 12 Months.Owner to transfer Flood Insurance remaining Owner to will provide remaining Paid Flood  that can  be transferred to new owner at closing.
